Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery lip-cup; interior: black-figure decoration consisting of draped female figure standing to right (upper body, raised left hand and lowered right arm remaining); at right, uncertain object, possibly part of antler; exterior glazed with reserved band.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0582) (Phase 1)
